The first leg of the popular Swannies Racing series is set to be hosted at Ysterberg on 21 March and two wheel and quad bike enthusiasts craving the action and the adrenaline rush are invited to enter for an unforgettable endurance race.
The endurance ride promises to test bikers’ skills and most importantly strength during the race.
There will be trophies for podium winners in the various quad and two wheel categories.
Registration costs R450 per bike for those participating in the four-lap 35 km race and R250 for the kiddies race consisting of an 8 km lap to be ridden over two hours.
Visitors and spectators will be charged R20 per person.
Registration can be done on the race day prior to the start which is scheduled for 10:00.
To get to the venue take the Geyser turn-off from the R101 towards Mokopane. Alternatively use the GPS location 24°02’07.6”S 29°14’06.9”E
Food and beverages will be on sale.
For more information contact Peet or Swannie Swanepoel on 083 469 0138 or 071 859 6924 respectively.
